arcus(PART 28): Batch 3 — UX polish + correctness

Six fixes from the audit. Two UI-heavy items (F5.2 Supabase-first
conversations, F7.4 memory edit UI) deferred — they need surgery in
ChatInterface and settings-card that risks regressions if rushed.

F4.2 — Confirmation prompt block gated on isBackgroundAgent OR skipConfirmations
Background-agent prompts were carrying the interactive "Confirmation
required before major actions" section even though there's no user
present. Now both isBackgroundAgent=true AND skipConfirmations=true
swap in the "Confirmations are OFF" block.

F4.3 — Tool inventory auto-derived from canonical map
INTEGRATION_CAPABILITIES was a parallel list in system-prompt.ts that
drifted from TOOL_INTEGRATION_MAP every time a new tool was added (the
PARTs 13-22 expansion was never reflected in the prompt). Extracted
the map to new lib/arcus/tool-integration-map.ts so system-prompt can
import it without circular deps. INTEGRATION_CAPABILITIES is now
generated from toolsForIntegration(integration) at module load —
adding a tool to the map automatically surfaces it to the LLM.

F7.2 — Tightened always/never auto-extraction
"Always loved that movie" was being saved as a behavioral rule because
the regex matched any "always X" / "never X" at message start. Now
requires an assistive-action verb after always/never (cc, bcc,
include, notify, send, schedule, draft, sign, reply, archive, etc).
"Always loved" → no match. "Always cc legal@" → match.

F9.4 — Report footer deep-links
Every cron-fired report now includes Edit / Pause / Run history
deep-links pointing at the user's dashboard with the agent_id pre-
selected. Suffix in REPORT_FORMAT_SUFFIX uses [INSERT_AGENT_ID]
which run-agent.ts substitutes at call time alongside the existing
[INSERT_CURRENT_UTC_TIMESTAMP] replacement.

F5.5 — Safe localStorage wrapper (hooks/useSafeLocalStorage.ts)
Browser localStorage caps at ~5-10MB. ChatInterface persists 35+
items including conversation message arrays — a long conversation
could throw QuotaExceededError silently on setItem. New
safeSetItem / safeGetItem / safeRemoveItem wrappers catch
QuotaExceededError, evict the oldest conversation_* entry by
lastUpdated, retry once. (ChatInterface migration to use these is a
follow-up — wrapper is exported and ready.)

F6.4 — Test-connection endpoint (/api/arcus/integrations/test)
GET ?provider=<gmail|gcal|notion|slack> makes one trivial API call
(Gmail profile, Calendar primary, Notion users/me, Slack auth.test)
and returns { ok, latency, detail } or { ok:false, reason }. Settings
UI can wire this to a "Test connection" button so the user knows
whether a connector is actually working without trying a dependent
tool.

Type-check clean.

